text: Nothing much in this plaza. Majority of the units were vacated, with the remaining consisting mostly of hardware shops. Even with such low footfall, one has to pay $0.20 to use the toilet. Money aside, you have to get the key from the security at level 1 even though you could be in other parts of the building.
Not much things to do here because itâ€™s really quiet

Not a review about the plaza itself, but rather the rooftop parking. Perhaps a hidden gem in terms of parking since the streets below are incredibly busy and almost never has an available car space. The carpark itself has an old and narrow entrance/exit and is dimly light at night, therefore not anyone's first choice which means there's usually space available! Just park and take the lift from level 4 :)
During the 60's it was one of the top plazas now only a few maby 40% die hard shops left, sad..

It's old Plaza located near to Kitchener road, have many offices including shops, consultancy & airlines office (US Bangla Airlines).

Can go to Mustafa center which is side by.
